{"questionId":"13122","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The voltage <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"v\">\n  <mi>v</mi>\n</math></span> in a circuit is given by the equation</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"v\\left( t \\right) = 3\\,{\\text{sin}}\\left( {100\\pi t} \\right)\">\n  <mi>v</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>t</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>sin</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>100</mn>\n      <mi>π</mi>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t \\geqslant 0\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n  <mo>⩾</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;where <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span> is measured in seconds.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down the maximum and minimum value of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"v\">\n  <mi>v</mi>\n</math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"color:#999;font-size:90%;font-style:italic;\">* This question is from an exam for a previous syllabus, and may contain minor differences in marking or structure.</p><p>3,&nbsp;−3&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13122","referenceCode":"19M.2.AHL.TZ1.H_10a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Write down the maximum and minimum value of v .","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 3— Geometry and trigo